choices.text:
what are the verb tenses?
The verb tenses in this passage are as follows:

1. Present simple - "I am a human" (referring to an ongoing state or fact)
2. Past simple - "We discovered fire" (describing a completed action in the past with no indication of repetition)
3. Future simple - "One day, we will discover electricity" (predicting a future event that is expected to occur)
